Package org.neo4j.token

Class DelegatingTokenHolder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.token.AbstractTokenHolderBase
      • org.neo4j.token.DelegatingTokenHolder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TokenHolder
    public class DelegatingTokenHolder
extends AbstractTokenHolderBase
    Keeps a registry of tokens using TokenRegistry. When asked for a token that isn't in the registry, delegates to a TokenCreator to create the token, then stores it in the registry.

      • getOrCreateIds

        public void getOrCreateIds​(String[] names,
                           int[] ids)
                    throws KernelException
        Description copied from interface: TokenHolder
        Resolve the ids of the given token names into the array for ids.

        Any tokens that don't already have an id will have one created for it.

        Note that this only looks at public tokens. For internal tokens, use TokenHolder.getOrCreateInternalIds(String[], int[]).

        Throws:
        KernelException
